The paper deals with action recognition tasks using unsupervised methods and proposes a new approach for action proposal ranking. The paper leverages image-based action detectors and motion information to select optimal combinations of sub-proposals from different proposals. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses dynamic programming and graph optimization schemes, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its approach on publicly available datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
